The Government of the French Republic, on the one hand, and the Government of the Republic of the Philippines on the other, hereinafter referred to as the "Parties".

DRAWING ON the importance of international cooperation to foster the production and sharing of new knowledge;

RECOGNIZING their mutual interest in developing and strengthening cooperation in scientific and technological research between France and the Philippines;

CONSIDERING the importance of structuring scientific and technological cooperation between France and the Philippines with the establishment of a Hubert Curien

Partnership in order to support the mobility of researchers and to facilitate the establishment of joint research projects;

RECALLING the cultural and historical ties between the French Republic and the

Republic of the Philippines, as demonstrated by the Agreement on Scientific and

Technical Cooperation and the Agreement of Cultural Cooperation between the

Government of the French Republic and the Government of the Republic of the

Philippines, both signed at Paris on 18 November 1978; as well as the Memorandum of Understanding on France-Philippines Cooperation in the area of Higher Education and Research signed on 26 February 2015;

CONSIDERING the desire of the two Parties to combine their efforts to encourage cooperation in the field of scientific research, with a view to improving knowledge and developing collaborations between France and the Philippines;

Have agreed as follows:

Article 1 - Purpose

The purpose of this Agreement is to establish a bilateral scientific cooperation programme called the French-Philippine Hubert Curien Partnership "Science for the

People", hereinafter referred to as "the programme".

The purpose of the programme is to support the scientific mobility of researchers during the implementation of jointly selected research projects aimed to:

• Support the development and consolidation of bilateral partnerships between scientific research institutions in France and in the Philippines;

• Support cooperative research projects;

• Promote the exchange of expertise and the sharing of knowledge, while respecting the right to intellectual property;

• Promote the mobility of university research fellows and researchers, especially young researchers;

